Write a java program to find factorial of a number in java?
:::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::
!2= 2*1    =2
!3= 3*2*1  = 6
!4= 4*3*2*1= 12


::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::
Step1.Take a number variable.
Step2.Take one variable and initialized it 1.
Step3:Iterate upto that number to find  factorial and store it n fact variable.
Step4.Finally print variable.
:::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::
package io.javabrains;

public class FactorialNumber {
	public static void main(String[] args) {
		int inputNumber = 5;
		int fact= 1;
		for(int i=1;i<= inputNumber; i++){
			fact= fact *i;
		}
		System.out.println("Factorial Number: "+fact);
	}
}
:::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::;;;
Factorial Number: 120
